Class RepositoryVersionedOutputStream

                  org.ndnx.ndn.io.RepositoryVersionedOutputStream
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable, Flushable
public class RepositoryVersionedOutputStream
extends NDNVersionedOutputStream

A subclass of NDNVersionedOutputStream which writes its segments to a repository, using versioned names. If the specified name includes a version, it will write that specific version; otherwise it will add a version to the name of the stream it writes. If the constructor is called with the boolean local set to true, the stream will be written to the repository on the local device. If no repository is available, it will throw an exception. Data written using this class can be read using a normal NDNVersionedInputStream; that class doesn't care whether its content comes from a repository or a cache (or a mix of the two).
